<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98620095234876></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98620095234876><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98620095234876>Some advice on Brass</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98620095234876#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39960><span id= >Adept</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 2nd 4:42 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello fellow musicians!<br><br>Going to throw out some advice on Brass, how to get it up easily.&nbsp;&nbsp;Oddly for some reason you get the spell way before you get any song to improve brass.  Skill comes to you at 11, and first song at 18.  This is where it gets hard.  That first song is an AOE, DOT, ac reduction.  It only activates when u are near another PC (non party member excluding pets) (I could be wrong here but please post if I am, never got a skill raise that wasn't triggered by the song going off on something), NPC's and monsters.  I have seen some posts on how hard it is to get this skill up, and it truly requires some dedication and diligence.  How I got mine up was to take a trip back to Kelethin.  Yes it was my newbie starting area.  That is what makes this area so good.  The guards do not often roam far from their posts (unlike Misty thicket &lt;shudder&gt;), which is good.  The last thing you want is some unsuspecting (and unforgiving) guard wandering into your singing are, for he will chastise you outright (this song is no different from chords).  The spawn rate of the area is excellent as well, not really robbing newbies of any kills.  I found between activating the song by newbies, and monsters brought it up to 85 in a day.  Now that took about 8 hours of work, but until you put the time into it, you will see that any attempt to play it with th horn results in a missed note.  So basically all I did was start the song (after about 20 tries) and ran around killing things.  If you were a newbie to the zone before get your revenge on evrything, as you will see wasps, spiders, black wolf's die the first time that song hits them ;-). Keep Selo's handy (and a drum) for that incidental encounter with a guard.  Also watch out for the Faerie guards, I haven't decided id I want to lower faction with them, so when in doubt I left them alone.  That, my budding musicians is it.  I gave up one day of leveling (not all that bad), for one day of training in Kelethin.  Oh and I raked in about 2pp an hour if you are dilligent enough to pick up all of the stackable items.  Also a good time to bring up that tailoring skill as you will have both spider silks, and wolf pelts to work with.  Good luck my friends and I hope this helps some!<br><br>Tynael<br>Bard of the 19 Song<br>Ayonae Ro<br>  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
