	   <tr><td colspan=2>Can't say much about twinks or newb's in general.&nbsp;&nbsp;What I can say, is group with people willing to listen.  I cannot stress enough the importance of a party that is on a Team level vice individual hunter.  If you find yourself repeating things that concern you leave the party is my suggestion.  Too many times I died later due to another massive pull despite my complaints prior.  I do however recommending fighting in EC.  Like you said excellent exp, good loot, and you can easily do several quests there.  The sword shipment quest (everything is at orc camp 1 for this), and the Deathfist belts (bounty really).  The swords for the sword quest (there are three swords on the ground in 3 out of the 4 tents).  The fourth sowrd is on the weaponsmith.  Complete the shipment per quest, and take the resulting sword back to the guy that gave you the quest, and whola, faction AND a great newbie weapon to start with.  If you have a better one, give it to a newb that isn't begging (can't condone begging for things), and watch him be happy with that slightly better weapon.  Enjoy all, and careful out there ;-).<br><br>Tynael<br>Bard of the 19th song<br>Ayonae Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
