	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you read the text manual in your Everquest directory you will find out about the /pause command. Heres how you use it.<br><br>Here is an example of a string that cast a spell then sit down. <br><br>/sit off<br>/pause 100,/cast 1<br>/sit on<br><br>Here is an explination of what the commands do:<br><br>/sit off&nbsp;&nbsp;"will stand you up if your sitting down"<br>/pause 100,/cast 1 "will cast song 1 then wait 10 sec you must have the comma for this to work"<br>/sit off "will sit you down after you cast"<br><br>Hope this helps some if you have any questions just look for the eq manual.txt in your everquest directory.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

