	   <tr><td colspan=2>As soon as I popped into Queynos with my shiny, eager, brand spanking new bard, I went to the gate near the newbie area.<br>Now, the manual and the Prima book advocate begging like mad to get money. That kind of annoys people and a bard should never be annoying.<br>But it is very much in character to "put down a hat" so to speak and entertain for donations. Just announce (shout) that you will be offerring comedy at "location" and "thank you in advance for showing your appreciation" (read: monetary donations). This is a good way to pay for that first song and some other things.<br>I advise that you have a good, clean joke book handy. EQ humor realy sells well(i.e. If you kill a fairie, do you lose faction with San Fransisco?). Stand off to the side but in clear view of those going through the gate. Mention often, but not too much, your thanks for the "monetary display of appreciation for my lowly talents". You will soon see your trade window pop up often with gifts.<br>If a noticeable character goes by make a friendly comical comment about them.<br>Remember you are there to entertain but do not swamp the chat window.<br>I collected a lot of cash and made numerous aquaintances doing this. Its not begging and its very in character. I still get friendly comments by people who saw me in Queynos back then. I still periodically put on a performance in known congregatory areas. I even got a friendly nod from a wanderring GM and its always good to have them on your side.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
