	   <tr><td colspan=2>Its not the number of available quests but how you manage the quest available. Here is what I do in Kelethin/GF area:<br>Assuming you have Selos (level 5) this is a quick way to get fairly easy exp. In Kelethin, at orc hill (not Crushbone), kill green orcs and collect orc belts. Once you get 4 or more (more is obviously better) crank on Selos and travel to Kaladim through Butcherblock. Talk to and give the belts to Canaloe. You get items to sell, cash and exp. On the way out of the building but just vefore the zone to BB, in front of a tavern, there is a Bard, Kilan Oresinger i think. Talk to him and get the mail quest to Kelethin. Travel back to Kelethin.<br>Along the way kill spiderlings and collect silks, at least 4. When you get back to the bard area in Kelethin deliver your mail, get cash and exp. Talk to and give silks to the female bard npc to the left of the bard you gave the mail to. She will ask about the silks. Give her the 4 at teh same time, get a drum and exp. Sel thedrum unless you need it.<br>Start cycle over.<br>Depending on how fast you collect belts you could gain a lot of exp in a relatively short amount of time.<br>I myself dont deliver belts till I get 16 of them.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
